Project Overview

This project demonstrates the design and implementation of a network using Variable Length Subnet Masking (VLSM) and static routing in Cisco Packet Tracer.
The objective was to optimize IP address allocation starting from a single Class C network and to interconnect multiple LAN segments efficiently, minimizing address waste and ensuring proper routing between subnets.

Goals

Design an IP addressing plan using VLSM based on the number of required hosts in each subnet.

Configure routers and switches to interconnect four LANs and one point-to-point link.

Implement static routes for inter-network communication.

Test connectivity between all hosts using ping and verify routing paths.

