Project Description â€“ VLSM Subnetting and Static Routing

In this scenario, I applied subnetting using VLSM (Variable Length Subnet Masking).
Starting from a single IP network, the goal was to optimize and distribute IP addresses efficiently among different local networks according to their host requirements.

Each subnet must reserve one address for the network ID and one for the broadcast, so the formula used to calculate the number of available hosts is:

